te, 20% click rate Post-Webinar Sequence Replay Email (24 hours after) Subject: \"Did you miss the solution? (Replay + special offer)\" Replay access + testimonials 40% open rate, 12% click rate Final Urgency (48 hours after) Subject: \"Final hours: Your perimenopause transformation (50% off)\" Last chance messaging + bonuses 35% open rate, 8% click rate Webinar Structure & Conversion Tactics 90-Minute Webinar Outline Opening (15 minutes) Personal perimenopause story Credibility markers (certifications, media mentions) Agenda and expectations Engagement poll: \"Rate your current energy level 1-10\" Content Section (45 minutes) Trigger 1: Hidden thyroid dysfunction Trigger 2: Adrenal fatigue cascade Trigger 3: Gut microbiome disruption Trigger 4: Toxic load accumulation Trigger 5: Nutrient depletion patterns Case Studies (15 minutes) Before/after transformations Specific symptom improvements Timeline expectations Offer Presentation (15 minutes) Problem recap Solution positioning Bonuses and guarantees Urgency and scarcity Clear call-to-action Conversion Optimization Tactics During Webinar: Interactive polls every 15 minutes Chat engagement with moderator Urgency: \"Only 100 spots available\" Social proof: \"Sarah from Texas just purchased\" Post-Webinar: Immediate replay access 48-hour cart open period Graduated discount structure Bonus stacking strategy Implementation Resources Required Tools & Platforms GoHighLevel: Landing pages, email automation, sales funnels Zoom: Webinar hosting (up to 1,000 attendees) Canva Pro: PDF creation and ad graphics Facebook Ads Manager: Traffic generation Google Analytics: Tracking and optimization Content Creation Resources Perimenopause symptoms research: Mayo Clinic, Harvard Health Supplement protocols: Examine.com, PubMed studies Meal planning: Anti-inflammatory nutrition guidelines Exercise routines: Hormone-balancing workouts Legal & Compliance Health disclaimers: \"Not medical advice\" statements Income disclaimers: \"Results 