Financial Performance Analysis Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC): $4.27 ($500 ÷ 117 customers) Customer Lifetime Value (CLV): $403 average order value Return on Ad Spend (ROAS): 94.3x Profit Per Customer: $399 Break-even Point: 1.25 customers needed Marketing Strategy (COMPLETE) Multi-Channel Approach 1. Facebook Ads Strategy ($200 total) Cold Traffic (75% - $150): Interest targeting women 35-50 with menopause, fatigue, hormone health interests Warm Traffic (25% - $50): Retargeting website visitors and video viewers Expected Results: 2,000 leads at $0.10 cost per lead 2. Email Marketing Sequence Pre-Webinar: 6-email nurture sequence building anticipation Post-Webinar: 4-email sales sequence with urgency tactics Performance: 45-65% open rates, 8-25% click rates 3. Content Marketing Blog Posts: SEO-optimized perimenopause content Social Media: Educational posts with lead magnet promotion Video Content: Symptom awareness and solution previews 4. Partnership Strategy Health Influencers: Revenue-share partnerships Medical Professionals: Endorsements and referrals Supplement Brands: Cross-promotion opportunities Conversion Optimization Tactics Landing Page Elements: Compelling headline addressing fatigue and energy issues Video testimonials from real women Social proof with specific results Clear value proposition and instant access Email Sequence Optimization: Subject line testing for maximum open rates Personalization based on download behavior Progressive urgency building toward webinar Scarcity messaging for limited webinar spots Webinar Registration Optimization: Multi-step registration process Calendar integration for reminders Bonus incentives for attendance Mobile-optimized registration flow Complete Webinar Script Collection LIVE WEBINAR SCRIPT (90 Minutes) - Jason Fladlien Style [OPENING - 15 Minutes] \"Hi everyone, and welcome to what I promise will be the most eye-opening 90 minutes of your perimenopause journey. I'm [Your Name], and I'm absolutely thrilled you're here. Before we dive in, I want you to know something important: What you're about to learn in the next 90 minutes isn't available anywhere else. This isn't recycled information you can Google. These are the 5 hidden triggers that 99% of women - and even most doctors - completely miss. Let me ask you something... How many of you logged on today feeling exhausted? Type 'TIRED' in the chat if that's you right now. [PAUSE for chat responses] I see hundreds of you saying 'TIRED'... And here's what I want you to understand: That exhaustion isn't normal. It's not just part of getting older. And it's definitely not something you have to live with. My name is [Your Name], and I've helped over 3,000 women transform their perimenopause experience. But I wasn't always an expert on this topic. I was actually a victim of it. Three years ago, I was where many of you are right now. I was 42, successful in my career, but privately falling apart. I was so exhausted I could barely function. I was gaining weight no matter what I did. My brain felt like it was wrapped in cotton. My doctor told me it was 'just stress' and handed me an antidepressant. But I knew something else was happening. And after 18 months of research, working with functional medicine doctors, and testing dozens of protocols, I discovered the 5 hidden triggers that were stealing my energy and destroying my health. Once I addressed these triggers, everything changed. Within 30 days, my energy returned. Within 60 days, I'd lost 15 pounds. Within 90 days, I felt like myself again. And that's exactly what I'm going to share with you today. Now, I want to be crystal clear about something: This isn't a medical presentation. I'm not a doctor, and nothing I share today is meant to diagnose or treat any condition. What I'm sharing is educational information and my personal experience. Always consult your healthcare provider before making any changes. But here's what I can promise you: By the end of this webinar, you'll understand why you've been struggling, and you'll have a clear roadmap to reclaim your energy and vitality. Let me show you what we're going to cover: The 5 Hidden Perimenopause Triggers: The Thyroid Deception (this affects 85% of women) The Adrenal Exhaustion Trap The Gut-Brain Energy Hijack The Toxic Load Accumulation The Nutrient Depletion Cascade Each of these triggers creates a domino effect that leaves you feeling exhausted, foggy, and frustrated. But more importantly, I'm going to show you exactly how to address each one. Before we start, I want to see where everyone is. In the chat, rate your current energy level from 1-10, where 1 is 'I can barely function' and 10 is 'I have abundant energy all day.' [PAUSE for responses] I'm seeing mostly 2s, 3s, and 4s. That's exactly what I expected. By the end of our time together, you'll understand why your energy is so low, and you'll have the tools to get it back to an 8, 9, or even 10. One more thing before we dive in: I know your time is valuable. You could be doing a million other things right now. The fact that you're here tells me you're serious about solving this. So I'm going to give you everything I've got. At the end of this presentation, I'll share details about my complete system - the exact protocols I used to transform my own health and that I've used with over 3,000 women. But right now, let's focus on the education. Are you ready to discover what's really causing your exhaustion?\" [CONTENT SECTION - 50 Minutes] TRIGGER 1: The Thyroid Deception (12 minutes) \"Let's start with the most common trigger that affects 85% of women in perimenopause: The Thyroid Deception. Here's what's happening: Your doctor runs a TSH test, it comes back 'normal,' and you're told your thyroid is fine. But TSH is just one piece of the puzzle. It's like judging a movie by watching only the trailer. The real issue is that during perimenopause, your thyroid doesn't just slow down - it becomes inefficient. You might have normal TSH but your T3 (the active thyroid hormone) is low. Or you might have reverse T3 blocking your thyroid receptors. Sarah from Michigan wrote to me: 'I had five different doctors tell me my thyroid was fine, but I knew something was wrong. After following your protocol, my energy increased 300% in just 6 weeks.' The key is understanding that perimenopause creates a perfect storm for thyroid dysfunction: Estrogen dominance blocks thyroid hormone receptors Cortisol imbalance affects thyroid conversion Nutrient deficiencies prevent proper thyroid function This is why the standard 'take Synthroid' approach fails so many women. You're not addressing the root cause. In my system, I show you the exact tests to request from your doctor - not just TSH, but Free T3, Free T4, Reverse T3, and thyroid antibodies. I also share the specific nutrients and lifestyle changes that support optimal thyroid function during perimenopause. Who here has been told their thyroid is 'normal' but still feels exhausted? Type 'NORMAL' in the chat. [PAUSE for responses] I see hundreds of you. This is exactly why I created this system. The standard approach is failing women like you every single day.\" TRIGGER 2: The Adrenal Exhaustion Trap (12 minutes) \"The second trigger is what I call The Adrenal Exhaustion Trap. This is where your stress response system literally burns out from years of chronic stress. Here's the thing: Your adrenal glands don't know the difference between being chased by a tiger and dealing with a demanding boss, relationship stress, or financial pressure. They respond the same way - by pumping out cortisol. During perimenopause, this system becomes even more fragile because: Your progesterone (which balances cortisol) drops Your sleep quality deteriorates Your blood sugar becomes unstable The result? You wake up exhausted, crash around 3 PM, and feel wired but tired at night. Lisa from Texas shared: 'I thought I was lazy because I needed a nap every afternoon. Turns out my adrenals were completely shot. Your protocol gave me steady energy all day for the first time in years.' The conventional approach is to push through with more caffeine, more exercise, more willpower. But that's like flooring the gas pedal when your engine is already overheating. Instead, you need to support your adrenal recovery with: Specific adaptogenic herbs Strategic meal timing Stress-reduction techniques Sleep optimization protocols I'll show you the exact supplements and timing that helped me go from needing 3 cups of coffee just to function to having natural energy all day. Type 'CRASH' in the chat if you experience that afternoon energy crash.\" TRIGGER 3: The Gut-Brain Energy Hijack (12 minutes) \"The third trigger is something most women never connect to their energy levels: The Gut-Brain Energy Hijack. Your gut produces 95% of your body's serotonin - the neurotransmitter that regulates mood, sleep, and energy. During perimenopause, declining estrogen disrupts your gut microbiome, creating a cascade of problems: Increased inflammation Poor nutrient absorption Neurotransmitter imbalances Blood sugar instability This is why you might feel foggy, anxious, or depressed along with being exhausted. It's not 'all in your head' - it's literally your gut talking to your brain. Jennifer from California told me: 'I had no idea my digestive issues were connected to my energy. After healing my gut with your protocol, my brain fog lifted and my energy soared.' The key is understanding that your gut health directly impacts: How well you absorb nutrients Your inflammatory response Your mood regulation Your sleep quality In my system, I share the exact gut-healing protocol that includes: Specific probiotics for perimenopause Healing foods and those to avoid Digestive enzyme protocols Inflammation-reducing strategies Who here struggles with digestive issues along with low energy? Type 'GUT' in the chat.\" TRIGGER 4: The Toxic Load Accumulation (7 minutes) \"The fourth trigger is one that's often overlooked: The Toxic Load Accumulation. Over the years, your body accumulates toxins from: Environmental pollutants Processed foods Household chemicals Personal care products During perimenopause, your body's natural detoxification systems become less efficient, creating a perfect storm. These toxins interfere with: Hormone production Cellular energy production Liver function Sleep quality The solution isn't extreme detox programs that stress your already-overwhelmed system. Instead, it's supporti"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=a7294ca2-7244-471b-bd24-9f0d686135f4","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=a7294ca2-7244-471b-bd24-9f0d686135f4"}]}]}]
